     Oct. 11 (Bloomberg) - Holger Schmieding, chief economist at
Berenberg Bank, says it would be difficult for the U.S. to cut 
its budget deficit without introducing higher consumption taxes.
Schmieding talks with Bloomberg's Ken Prewitt on Bloomberg 
Radio's "Bloomberg - The First Word."  (Source: Bloomberg)  Running time 08:10
 